dismissalText.commentary: Gautam Gambhir run out (Udana) 102 (101b 10x4 0x6 166m) SR: 100.99

dismissalComment.html: run-out, terrific work from Udana, he might not have done too well with the ball, but his slide-rule throw could well have taken this game out of India's grasp, Gambhir pushed that towards mid-on and set off for a quick single, Udana was onto the ball and a direct hit catches Gambhir short, third umpire was called for, but Sangakkara in the dressing room was already signalling that it was out even before the replays came up, that's the 14th time Gambhir has been run out

oh my goodness, all that build-up over Rohit v Tiwary, Rohit is gone for a golden duck, a full, swinging delivery from Malinga is too good for Rohit, he was looking to work it to the leg side, he misses and that strikes his just above the boot, and his critics will have plenty more to say now, and Malinga is doing his bit to silence those questioning his performances against India

there's the wicket Sri Lanka were looking for, Kohli was looking to punch that short of length ball off the back foot, he tapped it straight back to Herath, who gleefully accepts the chance, it ws looking very easy for the Indian batsmen over the past hour or so

headshotImage.longCaption: Zaheer Khan player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentTextItems.html: it's over, India have won, this is the highest successful chase at this stadium, Irfan launches a length ball to deep midwicket for four, he takes off helmet and jumps for joy

commentPostTextItems.html: India up 2-1 in the five-match series. Gambhir looked in terrific touch today, Kohli less so and Dhoni wasn't at his best either but the two of them put on important stands with Gambhir, when India looked on course for victory. But, as he has so many times, Malinga produced some magic deliveries to send back MSD and Rohit, and put Sri Lanka in charge. A direct hit then dismissed  Gambir, and India looked headed for defeat. They had some bits of luck though, with a few edged boundaries providing the early momentum for Raina and Irfan - Raina was dropped once as well, and a run-out chance was missed - before the two batsmen took charge. Raina had been piling on the runs at the end of the innings in recent ODIs, but usually when India were looking to set a target. This time, he was around to shepherd the chase, taking India home with an unbeaten 65 off 45. Irfan is in the team as a bowling allrounder, and has proved effective so far in the series, making a crucial unbeaten 34.

Suresh Raina is the Man of the Match. "I learnt over the years, how to bat when you need 8 an over, Gautam played very well early on, set the platform. I looked to play straight, not to play cross, I knew I could hit over cover, over midwicket, I also wanted to run hard. Credit goes to Gautam, he batted very well."

Mahela Jayawardene: "It was one of those days. They are a quality team, I thought we played a good game, just a few mistakes. Up front, we were not putting enough pressure in the chase. We bowled poorly (towards the end) and dropped Suresh as well. It's tough when you lose, but you try and re-focus for the next game. Sanga will get a good deserved break (smiles)."

Dhoni: "We had a chance, because Gautam was still batting, and we all had belief in Raina, we also had Irfan and Ashwin. I think those two wickets changed the game, Gautam did really well, we needed one of the top three to put in a performance like this. We need to improve our death bowling, and our fielding, but overall I was happy with our performance."
S Rajesh, our stats editor, has done a match report after several years. See how he fared here.
Thanks for all the mails today, and you all need to go a little easy on Rohit. See you in the fourth ODI.

commentTextItems.html: after several overs of calm batting, Irfan jumps down the track and looks to slog a short of length ball over the leg side, he misses, the crowd loves it and roars its appreciation, it's 3 off 3 now, Raina walks up and has a chat with Irfan
looks to hammer it through the off side, ends up sends it straight down the track, Mathews tries to field that one, but can't as it was too low for him and hit too hard, one run taken

commentPreTextItems.html: Mathews to bowl the final over. He hits sixes when needed in the final over, can he stop giving away six now?

commentTextItems.html: short of length ball is swatted towards deep midwicket, Raina gets two for his efforts
full ball is driven towards the bowler, Malinga fields and it is a dot ball, India need six off the final over

headshotImage.caption: Irfan Pathan player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Irfan Pathan player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentTextItems.html: Malinga keeps it full, Irfan jabs it towards point, a diving from the fielder then takes the pace off the ball but can't stop it, Irfan races back for the second
a full toss from Malinga, crunched down the ground, long-off does the fielding but can't prevent the second
full and outside off, crisply hit by Irfan, just needed to be placed better, can't beat Dilshan at backward point

another yorker, on off stump, raina manages to squeeze that out towards short cover, there's a direct hit this time, but Irfan has just made his ground, to make things worse for Sri Lanka, India sneak an overthrow as well
a yorker just outside off, Irfan has sensibly been taking the singles and turning over the strike to Raina in the past few overs, he does it again
another lofted hit from Raina, towards deep extra cover,Udana has to get across from long-off to cut it off, two more to India

headshotImage.caption: Irfan Pathan player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Irfan Pathan player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentTextItems.html: Raina launches that full ball towards sweeper cover, Tharanga moves across to field that one, Raina wanted three but settles for two
short of length ball on the leg stump, swatted towards deep square leg
Raina wanted to thump that through the off side as well, but edges it towards mid-on for a single
attempted slower ball loops towards Raina as a full toss, Raina backs away and sends that through the off side for a couple

commentPreTextItems.html: In the midst of all the Rohit v Tiwary talk, Raina's recent ODI form has gone un-noticed. Three half-centuries in five innings, and regularly providing India the momentum at the end of the innings in the recent past

commentTextItems.html: helps this to short fine leg for a single
full and outside off, guided towards deep point for one more

commentPostTextItems.html: Praveen: "c'mon guys give rohit a break! Literally or figuratively?;)" Hah!

dismissalText.commentary: Virender Sehwag c sub (SMSM Senanayake) b Perera 3 (6b 0x4 0x6 6m) SR: 50

dismissalComment.html: Sehwag falls early, looking to swing it through the cover but ends up giving an overhead catch to the substitute fielder at cover, as in the second match Perera removes Sehwag cheaply, Perera continues to find one-day cricket easy

dismissalText.commentary: Virat Kohli c & b Herath 38 (65b 2x4 0x6 80m) SR: 58.46

dismissalComment.html: there's the wicket Sri Lanka were looking for, Kohli was looking to punch that short of length ball off the back foot, he tapped it straight back to Herath, who gleefully accepts the chance, it ws looking very easy for the Indian batsmen over the past hour or so

dismissalText.commentary: MS Dhoni b Malinga 31 (49b 1x4 0x6 60m) SR: 63.26

dismissalComment.html: and what a comeback, one of those deadly yorkers that confound batsmen so often, Dhoni looked to squeeze that one out but can't get bat in the way, crashes into the stumps, once again Sri Lanka strikes just when a partnership seemed to be calmly guiding India's chase.

dismissalText.commentary: Rohit Sharma lbw b Malinga 0 (1b 0x4 0x6 1m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: oh my goodness, all that build-up over Rohit v Tiwary, Rohit is gone for a golden duck, a full, swinging delivery from Malinga is too good for Rohit, he was looking to work it to the leg side, he misses and that strikes his just above the boot, and his critics will have plenty more to say now, and Malinga is doing his bit to silence those questioning his performances against India

dismissalText.commentary: Gautam Gambhir run out (Udana) 102 (101b 10x4 0x6 166m) SR: 100.99

dismissalComment.html: run-out, terrific work from Udana, he might not have done too well with the ball, but his slide-rule throw could well have taken this game out of India's grasp, Gambhir pushed that towards mid-on and set off for a quick single, Udana was onto the ball and a direct hit catches Gambhir short, third umpire was called for, but Sangakkara in the dressing room was already signalling that it was out even before the replays came up, that's the 14th time Gambhir has been run out
